# Relish Website Internals

## Login flow (3 different domains)

1. `GET relish.ezcater.com/schedule` тЖТ redirects to `login.ezcater.com/relish/sessions/new`
2. Email page: input `#identity_email`, submit button `[name=commit]` (it's an `<input type=submit>`, not a `<button>`)
3. Redirects to `account.ezcater.com/u/login` (Auth0). Password: `#password`, submit: `button[name=action]`
4. Auth0 password field needs JS value injection тАФ `send_keys()` works but `nativeInputValueSetter` + dispatch is more reliable for special chars.
5. If MFA required: redirects to `account.ezcater.com/u/mfa-email-challenge`. Code input: `#code`, checkbox: `#rememberBrowser` (use JS click тАФ label overlays it), submit: `button[name=action][value=default]`
6. After MFA, redirects back to `relish.ezcater.com/schedule`

## MFA gotcha

Each login attempt generates a NEW MFA code. You MUST keep the same browser session alive while waiting for the code. Never kill the browser and re-login with a stale code.

## Cookie persistence

After MFA, save cookies with `driver.get_cookies()`. On next login, load them with `driver.add_cookie()` (navigate to the domain first). The "remember 30 days" checkbox means cookies skip MFA for a month.

## Key URLs

| Page | URL |
|------|-----|
| Schedule (today) | `/schedule` |
| Schedule (date) | `/schedule/YYYY-MM-DD` |
| Restaurant menu | `/schedule_entries/{entry_id}` |
| Order item page | `/schedule_entries/{entry_id}/order_items/new?menu_item_id={id}` |
| Order review | `/orders/{order_id}/review` |
| Order checkout | `/orders/{order_id}/checkout` (POST via form) |
| My orders | `/customer_orders` |
| Order detail | `/customer_orders/{order_id}/order_details` |
| Cancel order | `/customer_orders/{order_id}/confirm_cancel` (AJAX, data-remote) |
| Profile | `/user/edit` |
| Food preferences | `/food_preferences` |
| Payment methods | `/payment_methods` |

## Ordering flow (5 steps)

1. Navigate to restaurant menu: `/schedule_entries/{entry_id}`
2. Click item link (`a[href*='menu_item_id={id}']`) тЖТ opens Foundation reveal modal
3. Click `#add-to-cart-button` (value: "Add to cart - $X.XX") тЖТ adds to cart sidebar
4. "Continue to checkout" is in `div.continue-checkout a.button` тАФ inside a hidden cart dropdown, so extract its `href` via JS and navigate directly: `/orders/{order_id}/review`
5. On review page, click `turbo-frame button[type="submit"]` (class `place-order-*-btn`, text "Place your order for {day}") тЖТ places the order

## Cart management

- Cart items show "Remove | Edit" links in `div.cart-action-links`
- Remove is `a[data-method='delete'][data-remote='true']` тАФ use AJAX DELETE with CSRF token, not direct navigation
- CSRF token: `document.querySelector('meta[name="csrf-token"]').content`
- After removing items, `driver.refresh()` to reload the page

## Cancel order flow

- Cancel link is `a[href*='confirm_cancel']` with `data-remote="true"` inside order card
- Navigate to `/customer_orders`, find the cancel link for the order ID via `#customer_order_{id} a[href*='confirm_cancel']`
- Click via JS (`data-remote` links use AJAX), then look for confirmation button

## Schedule page selectors

- Subsidy amount: `div.subsidy-widget-right` (may need JS `textContent` тАФ `.text` can be empty in headless)
- Subsidy label: elements containing text "subsidy"
- Date tabs: `a[href*='/schedule/']`
- Restaurant cards: `a[href*='/schedule_entries/']` тАФ each card is a link wrapping the restaurant info
- Order tracking cards: `[class*='tracking-card']`

## Menu page selectors

Menu items are `<a>` links containing `menu_item_id` in the href. Two rendering styles exist:
- **Card-style**: `<a href="/schedule_entries/{id}/order_items/new?menu_item_id={id}">Item Name\n$Price</a>` тАФ name/price in link text
- **List-style**: `<a href="...?category_name=Appetizers&menu_item_id={id}">` тАФ name is in a child `div.item-details`

Use `a[href*='menu_item_id']` to find all items regardless of style.

## Item customization modal

Clicking a menu item link opens a Foundation reveal modal (`#menu-item-modal`). Inside:

- **Sizes**: `input[type="radio"][name="order_item[size_index]"]` with `data-price`. Value is the index (0, 1, ...).
- **Option groups**: `div.menu-item-section-header` has `<strong>Group Name</strong>` + `<span>(Required/Optional)</span>`.
- **Choices**: `input[type="checkbox"][name="options[{group_id}]choices[]"]` with `data-price` and `value`. Group ID is the number in the name attribute.
- **Required vs optional**: `data-required-checkbox-group` on `div.menu_choices_list`, and `(Required)` / `(Optional)` span text.
- **Add to cart button**: `input#add-to-cart-button` with value like "Add to cart - $11.99".
- **Notes**: `textarea[name="order_item[notes]"]` or `#order_item_notes`.

### Option types

| Type | HTML | Example |
|------|------|---------|
| Size | `input[type=radio]` name=`order_item[size_index]` | Small (0), Regular (1) |
| Extras | `input[type=checkbox]` name=`options[{id}]choices[]` | Pita +$1.49 |
| Substitution | `input[type=radio]` name=`options[{id}]choices[]` | Almond Butter instead of PB |

To select an option via Selenium: `driver.execute_script("arguments[0].click()", input_element)`.

## Junk text to filter

Headless Chrome renders font-test strings: `"word word word..."` and `"mmMwWLliI0fiflO&1"`. Always filter these from body text.
